        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 9:21PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 921 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles northeast of Clayton, or 6 miles east of Sky Valley, moving
west at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Sky Valley, Oconee State Park, Tallulah Gorge State Park, Pine
Mountain, Mountain Rest, and Long Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
